
[1]bondage

   BOND'AGE, n. Slavery or involuntary servitude; captivity; imprisonment;
   restraint of a person's liberty by compulsion. In ancient English law,
   villenage.

   1. Obligation; tie of duty.

   He must resolve not to be brought under the bondage of observing oaths.

   2. In scripture, spiritual subjection to sin and corrupt passions, or
   to the yoke of the ceremonial law; servile fear. Heb.2. Gal.2. Rom.8.
